# paint.type AI Manifest (Read First)

This is the root AI manifest for paint.type.

## Project

**NAME CLARIFICATION:** The *project* is named "paint.type" (similar to Paint.NET). The *GitHub repository* is named "paint-type" (GitHub does not allow dots in repository names). All references should use "paint.type" as the project name.

paint.type is a cross-platform open-source image editor in the spirit of Paint.NET.
Repo: metadatastician/paint-type. License: AGPL-3.0-or-later.
Contact: paint-type@pm.me. Status: pre-alpha — v0.2.0 Core Image Operations
closing (compositing primitives + UndoGraph + Layer model + brush engine +
pt_layer_* FFI all landed; ABI category fully proven; Rust CI green on main).
Only AffineScript → typed-wasm bridge remains, gated on
hyperpolymath/typed-wasm#127 + #130 (paint-type#39). Last updated: 2026-06-07.

## Authority Split

- Central protocol authority:
  `standards/session-management-standards/`
- Local integration authority (this repo):
  - `Justfile` session recipes
  - `session/dispatch.sh`
  - `session/custom-checks.k9`
  - `session/local-hooks.sh`
  - `coordination.k9`

## What Has Already Been Done (Do Not Redo)

- `src/interface/Abi/{Types,Layout,Foreign}.idr` — Idris2 ABI types + layout
  proofs + pt_* FFI wrappers
- `verification/proofs/idris2/ABI/{Platform,Compliance}.idr` +
  `verification/proofs/idris2/Pixel.idr` — ABI-3, ABI-5, TP-3 proofs (CI-checked)
- `src/interface/ffi/src/main.zig` — Zig libpt implementation; 23 exports
  (`pt_tile_*` + `pt_layer_*` + slot helpers)
- `src/interface/ffi/build.zig` — Zig build file
- `src/interface/ffi/test/integration_test.zig` — 29/29 passing integration tests
- `src/paint_core/` — Rust image core: 5 modules (lib, composite, undo, layer,
  brush). 11 compositing ops, persistent UndoGraph, Layer/LayerStack, Brush
  engine (BrushTip + Brush::stamp + Stroke). cargo test 98/98 + 1 doctest.
- `src/bridges/paint-type-{tile,layer}.twasm` — DRAFT typed-wasm schemas
  (not yet `tw build`-compilable; gated on hyperpolymath/typed-wasm#127 + #130;
  paint-type#39)
- `tests/aspect_tests.sh` — 7 aspects PASS (SPDX, dangerous-pattern, ABI/FFI
  contract, Rust panic-safety, RGBA16F constants, Idris2 ABI check, file-I/O)
- `tests/e2e.sh` + `src/paint_core/tests/e2e_pipeline.rs` — 9-stage E2E pipeline
- `src/paint_core/fuzz/` — 3 cargo-fuzz targets (pt_tile_blit, pt_tile_write_pixel,
  pt_layer_opacity); 30 s CI smoke per target via `.github/workflows/fuzz-smoke.yml`
- `.github/workflows/coverage.yml` + `tests/coverage.sh` — cargo-llvm-cov +
  best-effort kcov; reporting only, no gate
- `.github/workflows/rust.yml` — Rust CI (clippy / fmt / test); GREEN on main

## Architecture

- Desktop shell: Gossamer (linearly-typed webview)
- UI: Web (HTML/CSS/JS) in Gossamer
- Native image core: Ephapax (Rust, linear types, RGBA16F tiles)
- Bridge: AffineScript + typed-wasm
- Collaboration: Burble (WebRTC, sub-10ms), Groove (service discovery)

## Canonical Session Commands

- `intake repo <path>`
- `checkpoint change <path>`
- `verify maintenance <path>`
- `verify substantial <path>`
- `verify release <path>`
- `close planned <path>`
- `close urgent <path>`
- `recover repo <path>`
- `handover full <path>`
- `handover split <path>`
- `handover model <path>`
- `handover human <path>`

## Core Invariants

1. Keep protocol text centralized; do not duplicate full protocol specs here.
2. Keep local policy and hook behavior local to this repo.
3. Write runtime session artifacts in working repos (typically `.session/`).
4. Keep README/AUDIT/manifest claims synchronized with actual files.
5. All cross-language boundaries go through the Idris2 ABI + Zig FFI — no shortcuts.
6. Tile memory is linearly typed — no aliased mutable references to tile data.

## Key Local Files

- `AUDIT.adoc` (local audit gate summary)
- `README.adoc` (project overview)
- `EXPLAINME.adoc` (directory structure guide)
- `TOPOLOGY.adoc` (architecture topology)
- `ROADMAP.adoc` (milestone plan)
- `session/README.md` (session-binding usage)
- `.machine_readable/` (machine-readable repo policy/state files)

## Startup Checklist For Agents

1. Read `0-AI-MANIFEST.a2ml`.
2. Read `AUDIT.adoc`.
3. Read `.machine_readable/STATE.a2ml` for current phase and blockers.
4. Read `.machine_readable/MUST.contractile` before making any changes.
5. Use canonical session commands through `session/dispatch.sh` or Just aliases.
6. Do not touch `src/interface/Abi/`, `src/interface/ffi/`, or `src/paint_core/` without reviewing existing proofs and tests first.
7. Avoid claiming files/paths exist unless verified in this repository.
